body:
The following examples use the `listingsAndReviews` collection in the
`sample_airbnb` database. If you have the [sample data sets](available-sample-datasets) on your cluster, you can create a custom
MongoDB Search index for [geo](bson-data-types-geo) type and run the
example queries on your cluster. The [index builder](fts-tutorial-ref) contains
instructions for loading the [sample data sets](available-sample-datasets), creating an [index definitions](ref-index-definitions), and running MongoDB Search queries.

The following is a sample index definition for
indexing the `address.location` field in the `listingsAndReviews`
collection:

```json
{
  "mappings": {
    "fields": {
      "address": {
        "fields": {
          "location": {
            "indexShapes": true,
            "type": "geo"
          }
        },
        "type": "document"
      },
      "property_type": {
        "type": "token"
      }
    }
  }
}
```
